-- Romanian Utility Seeking Bids for Water System Upgrades
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-09-11T13:23:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/romanian-utility-seeking-bids-for-water-system-upgrades.html
Apa Oltenia SA, a water utility in
southern  Romania , is seeking bids to upgrade water and sewage
systems for about 84 million lei ($24 million), a European Union
procurement  document  showed.  Apa Oltenia plans to build a new well as well as expand and
rehabilitate the water supply system in Segarcea, a town in Dolj
county, through a 44 million-lei contract, the document showed.
Bids must be submitted by Nov. 6.  The utility is also seeking to expand and upgrade water and
wastewater systems in the town of Bailesti for 39.7 million lei.
Bids for that must be submitted by Nov. 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
